---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About | Market Research Notes" description="About this market research knowledge site and how it is maintained.">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Why this site exists</h1>
      <p class="lede">This site is a structured library of market research and analytics knowledge. It is designed to be practical rather than encyclopedic: clear definitions, decision support, workflow notes, and examples that can grow over time.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell card-grid">
      <article class="card"><h2>Audience</h2><p>People learning research design, analysts building repeatable workflows, and future-you needing a reliable reference point.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h2>Content model</h2><p>All long-form content is Markdown-backed, so new pages can be added without touching the shared layouts or routes.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h2>Publishing model</h2><p>The site is configured as a static Astro project that builds cleanly to GitHub Pages project-site output.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="panel content-panel">
        <h2>What to add next</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Replace placeholder demo blocks with screenshots or small teaching interactions.</li>
          <li>Expand the Sawtooth section when you have concrete setup notes to document.</li>
          <li>Add more glossary entries as repeated terms appear in methodology pages.</li>
          <li>Introduce a light theme later if it becomes a real user need.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
